---

[TestNaNCheck/alerting_rule_with_division_inside_sum_is_reported - 1]
- description: alerting rule with division inside sum is reported
  content: |
    - alert: foo
      expr: sum(foo / bar) > 0
  output: |
    2 |   expr: sum(foo / bar) > 0
                          ^^^
                          This aggregation can return NaN or Inf if any series for `bar` evaluates to zero.
  problem:
    reporter: promql/nan
    summary: unsafe division in aggregation
    details: |-
        Division by zero produces non-finite values in PromQL:

        - `0 / 0` returns `NaN`
        - `1 / 0` returns `+Inf`
        - `x % 0` returns `NaN`

        Even if only one out of many input series is `NaN` or `Inf`, the entire aggregation result
        becomes `NaN` or `Inf`, making all other valid series irrelevant.
        To avoid this, filter out zero-valued divisor series before division, for example:
        `sum(foo / (bar > 0))`
        See [promql/nan](https://cloudflare.github.io/pint/checks/promql/nan.html) for more details.
    diagnostics:
        - message: This aggregation can return NaN or Inf if any series for `bar` evaluates to zero.
          firstcolumn: 11
          lastcolumn: 13
          kind: 0
    lines:
        first: 2
        last: 2
    severity: 1
    anchor: 0

